The paper deals with information theoretic analysis of a coded caching system, which involves communication and storage aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves networked systems and communication protocols, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes a novel group-based centralized coded caching scheme, which involves optimization and algorithmic aspects, indicating the category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves caching and storage aspects, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves theoretical analysis and simulations, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
